==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faun
<hw>Faun</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Faunus</ets>,
fr. <ets>favere</ets> to be favorable. See <er>Favor</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Rom. Myth.)</fld> <def>A god of fields and shepherds, differing
little from the satyr. The fauns are usually represented as half goat
and half man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Satyr or <qex>Faun</qex>, or Sylvan.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fauna</ent>⟦br⟧
